      <TextArea fx:id="textArea" layoutX="73.0" layoutY="80.0" prefHeight="390.0" prefWidth="644.0" text="FAQs About the War Games Application&#10;&#10;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&#10;How can I create an army?&#10;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&#10;To create an army you have to press the &quot;Create Army&quot; Button. When creating an army you will have to choose &#10;an army name (you cannot change this after you have added units - you will have to reset the page and lose all &#10;progress). Enter values in the TextFields, the only valid input in the health and amount of units are numbers. Then&#10;press add units - you can delete units by selecting them and pressing the delete units button. When finished with&#10;creating your army press &quot;Save File&quot; and save the file where you would like on your local storage.  &#10;&#10;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&#10;How can I simulate a battle?&#10;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&#10;Firstly, you load each army by pressing the &quot;Load Army&quot; buttons. After that you have to choose a terrain.&#10;Lastly, you have to press the &quot;simulate battle&quot; button. The winning army will be displayed after the battle is done. &#10;&#10;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&#10;What is the difference between the unit types?&#10;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&#10;The different unit types has different attack damage, armour, attack bonus and magic resist.&#10;&#10;Infantry Unit: attack = 15, armour = 10, attack bonus = 2 and resist bonus = 1&#10;Ranged Unit: attack = 15, armour = 8, attack bonus = 3 and resist bonus = 2&#10;Cavalry Unit: attack = 20, armour = 12, attack bonus = 2 and resist bonus = 1&#10;Commander Unit: attack = 25, armour = 15, attack bonus = 2 and resist bonus = 1&#10;&#10;The bonuses do however change by a given terrain and throughout the battle&#10; &#10;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&#10;What is the meaning of the terrain and how do they effect the bonuses?&#10;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&#10;The selected terrain gives different attack bonuses and resist bonuses to each unit type. &#10;&#10;Infantry Unit: attack bonus = 5 (when fields is selected) and 2 (else). &#10;resist bonus = 4 (when fields is selected) and 1 (else).&#10;&#10;Ranged Unit: attack bonus = 5 (when hills is selected), 2 (when fields is selected) and 3 (when plains is selected).&#10;resist bonus = 6 (when 0 hits taken), 4 (when 1 hit taken) and 2 (else).&#10;&#10;Cavalry Unit: attack bonus = 9 (when 0 hits dealt and plains is selected), 6 (when 0 hits dealt and another &#10;terrain is selected) and 5 (when more than 0 hits dealt and plains is selected). resist bonus = 0 (when &#10;more than 0 hits taken and fields is selected) and 1 (when 0 hits taken and fields is selected).&#10;&#10;Commander Unit: attack bonus = 6 (when 0 hits dealt) and 2 (else). &#10;resist bonus = 0 (when 0 hits taken) and 1 (else).&#10;&#10;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&#10;How can I reset a battle?&#10;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&#10;You can either reset a battle from scratch (this will remove the loaded armies, or the remaining winner army), or&#10;reset the battle with the same armies. You can choose which one you would like by pressing the menu item on&#10;the menu bar under &quot;Reset Battle&quot;.&#10;&#10;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&#10;How many armies can battle against each other at the same time?&#10;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&#10;Currently, only two armies can battle against each other at the same time." />
